  (181, 'Magister\'s Regalia', 'misc', 'Mage', 'Tier 0 (Dungeon Set 1)', 'Tier 0 marked the dawn of class sets in World of Warcraft. Forged through drops in the most difficult dungeons of Classic-Stratholme, Scholomance, and Blackrock Spire-these blue-quality sets gave players their first taste of coordinated gearing. While they lacked raid-level stats, their 8-piece bonuses hinted at the specialization that future raid sets would embody. Collecting these pieces was the natural bridge from leveling dungeons into endgame raiding, and many raiders proudly wore them into Molten Core. <span class=\'set-note\'>(Patch 1.05)</span>', 8, 'T0', 70, 1),
